storyInfo: Somehow, the cycle of day and night returns to normal, and the Ink Spirits no longer fear the sunlight. They take to massacring the villagers while Mr. Nothing shows unexpectedly proficient martial arts in trying to protect the innocent, but still, he fails.

attributes.text: The haze is the blood of a city.
I once saw the silhouette of the moon made indistinct, leaving only a round mark as if carefully carved high above, the moonlight along its pierced boundaries flowing into the sky, smearing whole.
I once saw the home I loved taken by a sea of flames. I was forced across the hard mountains, from one peak to another.

I've seen the victims of famine gnawing away at each other. In times of fighting drenched in blood, taking place within a hair's distance, people can seem like nothing ever happened, look ahead of them, and walk on.
I've seen that long, long road. I used to puzzle over why everyone would choose the same path, why death is predestined, why we are only numbly walking down ways that will meet again.

I've seen the barrens and the verdant mountain waters. Seen friends who stumbled down once and so never climbed up again. Seen the looks in parents' eyes in that brief, brief moment they wanted to abandon their own.
The look in your eyes. The lofty, ice-cold, solitary look in your eyes.
More than a Catastrophe's onslaught, than your mother and father abandoning you, than struggling in starvation on the brink of death, it puts sorrow for you in me. The greatest of all sorrows.
Are you looking at me, or are you looking at yourself?
I remember—how I once asked you this.

attributes.content: Stay away! Get back!
attributes.name: Villager

attributes.content: It—it bit off my hand—ha, haha—why can't I feel any pain at all, why—
attributes.name: Villager

attributes.content: Gkhaa!
attributes.name: Ink Spirit

attributes.content: Eek—stay away!
attributes.name: Villager

attributes.content: Are you okay?!
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: Why did you only just come?! Why did nobody sound the bell?! Where'd the vigilant monk go?!
attributes.name: Villager

attributes.content: You know we trusted you, so we did what you said! Why! Why did my husband have to die?! How can you make up for that?! How?!
attributes.name: Villager

attributes.content: We'll talk when we're safe.
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: Waaahhh—mama, mama! Give my mama back!
attributes.name: Little Girl

attributes.content: Gkhaa!
attributes.name: Ink Spirit

attributes.content: Whoa, there! Even less close for comfort!
attributes.name: Mr. Nothing

attributes.content: M-Mister, mama, mama—
attributes.name: Little Girl

attributes.content: Gkhaa!
attributes.name: Ink Spirit

attributes.content: Let's ignore this fellow for now! There seems be something disastrous afoot outside! Young lady, hold on tight, we're going to slip out of here!
attributes.name: Mr. Nothing

attributes.content: Gkhaa—! Gkhaa!
attributes.name: Ink Spirit

attributes.content: Another one?!
attributes.name: Mr. Nothing

attributes.content: I can't—I can't deal with this!
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: Gkhaa—!
attributes.name: Ink Spirit

attributes.content: Gkh!
attributes.name: Ink Spirit

attributes.content: Where the hell did they all come from?!
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: Damnit, there's no way I can hold back this many—
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: Gkh...?
attributes.name: Ink Spirit

attributes.content: Though they may figures in a painting, there is no need to slaughter them all... observing such a scene only serves to inspire outbursts of sorrow.
attributes.name: Saga

attributes.content: Lava, I am here to watch this place. Thou would best hurry to take others to refuge.
attributes.name: Saga

attributes.content: You...
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: Worry not for me. I have traveled many times here. I have had all manner of thought on the future, anxieties indeterminate—
attributes.name: Saga

attributes.content: —but for that in front of me, I have never been one moment nor fraction irresolute.
attributes.name: Saga

attributes.content: Leave this to me.
attributes.name: Saga

attributes.content: Alright. Keep going east. When you're done, find me and we'll converge.
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: Understood!
attributes.name: Saga

attributes.content: Gkhaa!!
attributes.name: Ink Spirit

attributes.content: I am here! None shall come forward!
attributes.name: Saga

attributes.content: Those who pass this line—shall be cut down.
attributes.name: Saga

attributes.content: Waaahhh—
attributes.name: Little Girl

attributes.content: Ow, ow! My dear young lady! Might you be able to stop pulling on my hair!
attributes.name: Mr. Nothing

attributes.content: Mamaaa—mamaaaa—
attributes.name: Little Girl

attributes.content: Gkhaa!
attributes.name: Ink Spirit

attributes.content: These cretins only keep gkh-gkh-gkhing! How can things so bent on chasing you not spit out a human word or two?!
attributes.name: Mr. Nothing

attributes.content: Gkh...
attributes.name: Ink Spirit

attributes.content: ...DON'T... RUN...
attributes.name: Ink Spirit

attributes.content: Good heavens, I was only joking! You need not! You absolutely need not—!
attributes.name: Mr. Nothing

attributes.content: *whimper* Mister, l—look in front!
attributes.name: Little Girl

attributes.content: Eh?
attributes.name: Mr. Nothing

attributes.content: Yaaagh!
attributes.name: Villager

attributes.content: A—Are you that fortune-teller...? Where are the other two heroes?
attributes.name: Villager

attributes.content: Behind you, behind you!
attributes.name: Villager

attributes.content: Gkhaa!
attributes.name: Ink Spirit

attributes.content: Why did you bring it over here!? Think of something—think of something!
attributes.name: Villager

attributes.content: What can I possibly think of?!
attributes.name: Mr. Nothing

attributes.content: Lead them away from here, away!
attributes.name: Villager

attributes.content: *whimper* Waaahhhh, mama, mama—
attributes.name: Little Girl

attributes.content: Oh, just stop crying! Stop! Stop crying, girl!
attributes.name: Villager

attributes.content: Agh! Those things are looking at us! Get out of here, get out of—
attributes.name: Villager

attributes.content: Gkhaaaaaagh!
attributes.name: Ink Spirit

attributes.content: Huh...?
attributes.name: Villager

attributes.content: Y-You used your fan?
attributes.name: Villager

attributes.content: Hide yourselves further away.
attributes.name: Mr. Nothing

attributes.content: Gkhao? Gkhaa—
attributes.name: Ink Spirit

attributes.content: In one move...?!
attributes.name: Villager

attributes.content: Ao!?
attributes.name: Ink Spirit

attributes.content: A-Amazing...
attributes.name: Villager

attributes.content: Ow-Owie, it hurts so much, it hurts so much—just what are these things, and how can they look so soft, yet be so hard when striking them?
attributes.name: Mr. Nothing

attributes.content: Oh, stop goggling at me. The proverb puts it well; even a cornered burdenbeast will bite. Here, we'd best just hurry on our way!
attributes.name: Mr. Nothing

attributes.content: Gkhao...
attributes.name: Ink Spirit

attributes.content: Man alive, Nothing, your kickboxing work's not bad, but you've never done a rescue business like this, eh?
attributes.name: Kroos

attributes.content: Deal with the enemies in front of you without checking movement on your whole perimeter, and sooner or later you'll give yourself grief.
attributes.name: Kroos

attributes.content: Ah, ahahah... that was quite dangerous just now! My apologies for the grief I gave you, benefactor. Only thanks to you am I safe and sound.
attributes.name: Mr. Nothing

attributes.content: Alright, quick, go and get everyone left into shelter.
attributes.name: Kroos

attributes.content: Er, what about you, benefactor?
attributes.name: Mr. Nothing

attributes.content: Me? Don't you mind, I walk light as a feather. They won't ever notice me.
attributes.name: Kroos

attributes.content: (Can the single skill of light-footedness really explain that?!)
attributes.name: Mr. Nothing

attributes.content: And then... how do we cut down these Ink Spirit numbers fast...?
attributes.name: Kroos

attributes.content: Eyaah! Wh—what's that fire in the garden?
attributes.name: Villager

attributes.content: Hoo! This blaze soaring skyward makes quite a spectacle!
attributes.name: Saga

attributes.content: Ho? Could it be that the name 'Lava' held this exact meaning?
attributes.name: Saga

attributes.content: Lavaaa.
attributes.name: Kroos

attributes.content: Confirm the extent of all enemy scatter in the vicinity for me.
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: This big of an arena?
attributes.name: Kroos

attributes.content: I'm worried about the surrounding buildings getting caught up, so I've been sort of keeping my Arts tied down...
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: ...but there's just too many enemies. If we keep dragging this out, I'm concerned casualties are going to end up tough to estimate.
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: Roger. Special times, special methods, right.
attributes.name: Kroos

attributes.content: I'll find a high vantage point. You focus on casting.
attributes.name: Kroos

attributes.content: I'll help you sort all the ones outside your Arts range. I guarantee I'm not gonna miss a single one.
attributes.name: Kroos

attributes.content: Good.
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: I'll submit the mission report afterwards... after all, it's not just the Infected that Rhodes Island helps.
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: Infected...?
attributes.name: Kroos

attributes.content: What's up?
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: Huh... nothing, actually. By the way, Lava.
attributes.name: Kroos

attributes.content: You seen Mr. Umbrella-Boiler anywhere?
attributes.name: Kroos
